 front \nface of the prism. Zhuo centered in frame, head and upper chest visible, \noccupying 40–50% of frame height — appearing small and isolated within \nthe vast dark space. Glass prism walls visible on both sides; top edge \nof prism in upper frame; floor visible in lower third. Camera at eye \nlevel, horizontal.\n\nMonochromatic cyan-blue palette throughout. Extremely low-key, underexposed. \nHeavy volumetric fog filling the entire space — creates massive bloom and \nglow effect around all light sources and around Zhuo's silhouette, \nsoftening all edges. Single top-down spotlight inside the prism, cold \nwhite with strong cyan cast — the fog causes the light to bloom outward \nrather than fall as a hard pool. Zhuo's face is mostly in dark shadow \nbut retains subtle cool definition — do not light the face directly, \nlet the fog and ambient cyan define the silhouette. No fill on right \nside of face. Thin cold rim suggestion on left jaw edge only.\n\nEnvironment beyond the prism: vast, dark, hazy infinite void — near-total \ndarkness with residual cyan atmosphere. Minimalist, sterile, and haunting \nmusic video aesthetic. The glass prism is nearly invisible — perceptible \nonly as thin edge refractions. Ghost image of Zhuo visible through the \nglass — approximately 30% opacity, 4% lateral offset, cooler temperature, \nedges softened by fog.\n\nCamera drifts slowly left to right over 5 seconds, 6–8% of frame width. \nGhost and real figure reach maximum separation at 2.5 seconds, then begin \nclosing. Expression: stoic, internally present, mouth very slightly open — \nlips parted 2–3mm. Eyes forward, slightly unfocused. Stillness at 0–2 sec; \neyes shift 15° left then return at 2 sec; slow exhale visible only in jaw \nrelease at 3–5 sec. Clip ends on held stillness. All movement at 40–50% \nspeed. Maintain exact appearance from @Image1. Consistent character, no \ndrift. Do not make glass glow independently. Background must read as vast \ndark void.","16:9","5"